assemblage.p:
The absolute value of x is defined by
            \abs{x} =
                \begin{cases}
                x \amp \text{if } x\ge 0\\
                -x  \amp \text{if } x\lt 0
                \end{cases}

li.p:
Eight basic functions and their graphs are important in applications:
        f(x)=x~~~~~~f(x)=\abs{x}~~~~~~f(x)=x^2~~~~~~f(x)=x^3
            f(x)=\sqrt{x}~~~~~f(x)=\sqrt[3]{x}~~~~~~f(x)=\dfrac{1}{x}~~~~~~f(x)=\dfrac{1}{x^2}
